\begin_inset Formula $\succeq_{1}$
\end_inset

 is more ambiguity averse than 
\begin_inset Formula $\succeq_{2}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(ii) 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{1}=u_{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{1}^{*}\leq c_{2}^{*}$
\end_inset

 (provided 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{1}=u_{2}$
\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Maximal ambiguity aversion happens when 
\begin_inset Formula $c^{*}(p)=0$
\end_inset

 that is Maxmin preferences.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
