\begin_layout Subsection
Relation of market beliefs and decision theory beliefs.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Maxmin Expected Utility Preferences MEU.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is a pair: set of priors 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 and a utility index 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This utility representation is equivalent to the Choquet when 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 has additional structure as the core of a convex capacity.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To derive a simple characterization the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi(f)$
\end_inset

 for MEU preferences, let 
\begin_inset Formula $U:\mathbb{R}_{+}^{S}\rightarrow\mathbb{R}^{S}$
\end_inset

 be the function 
\begin_inset Formula $U(f):=(u(f(1)),\cdots,u(f(S)))$
\end_inset

 giving ex post utilities in each state.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For each 
\begin_inset Formula $f\in\mathbb{R}_{+}^{S}$
\end_inset

 let
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
M(f):=argmin_{p\in P}E_{p}u(f)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
be the set of minimizing priors realizing the utility of 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $V(f)=E_{p}u(f)$
\end_inset

 for each 
\begin_inset Formula $p\in M(f)$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using standard envelope theorem, we can express the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi(f)$
\end_inset

 as follows.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Define 
\begin_inset Formula $DU(f)$
\end_inset

 the 
\begin_inset Formula $S\times S$
\end_inset

 diagonal matrix, with 
\begin_inset Formula $U(f)$
\end_inset

 in the diagonal.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (2)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\succeq$
\end_inset

 be a MEU preference represented by a set of priors 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 an a concave, strictly increasing, and differentiable utility index 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then 
\begin_inset Formula $\succeq$
\end_inset

 is a convex preference and 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\pi(f)=\left\{ \frac{q}{||q||}|q=pDU(f)\quad for\quad some\quad p\in M(f)\right\} 
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In particular 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi(x)=P$
\end_inset

 for all constant acts 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Follows from Proposition 3 by noting that MEU is the special case where
 
\begin_inset Formula $c^{*}(p)=0$
\end_inset

 if 
\begin_inset Formula $p\in P$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $c^{*}(p)=\infty$
\end_inset

 if 
\begin_inset Formula $p\notin P$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
VARIATIONAL PREFERENCES.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Introduced by MMR variational preferences have the representation 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V(f)=min_{p\in\Delta S}[E_{p}u(f)+c^{*}(p)]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $c^{*}:\Delta S\mapsto[0,\infty]$
\end_inset

 is a convex, lower semicontinuous function, grounded 
\begin_inset Formula $c(p)=0$
\end_inset

 for at least one 
\begin_inset Formula $p\in\Delta S$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ambiguity index or cost of choosing a prior.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Define 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
M(f):=argmin_{p\in\Delta S}\{E_{p}[u(f)]+c^{*}(p)\}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
be the set of priors minimizing the objective functional.
 Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $V(f)=E_{p}u(f)+c^{*}(p)$
\end_inset

 for each 
\begin_inset Formula $p\in M(f)$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset

(3) Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\succeq$
\end_inset

 be a variational preference for which 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

 is concave, increasing, and differentiable.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $\succeq$
\end_inset

 is a convex preference and 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\pi(f)=\left\{ \frac{q}{||q||}|q=pDU(f)\quad for\quad some\quad p\in M(f)\right\} 
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In particular 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi(x)=\{p\in\Delta S|c^{*}(p)=0\}$
\end_inset

 for all constant acts 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{rem}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 At a constant act 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi(x)$
\end_inset

 is equal to the set of probabilities for which 
\begin_inset Formula $c^{*}$
\end_inset

, the cost of choosing a prior, is zero.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For Multiplier preferences, one has a singleton as solution 
\begin_inset Formula $\{q\}$
\end_inset

 consisting on the reference probability.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{rem}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
SMOOTH MODEL.
 KMM.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The representation is 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V(f)=E_{u}\phi(E_{p}u(f))
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is interpreted as a probability distribution on the set of probability
 measures 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi:\mathbb{R}\mapsto\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $u:\mathbb{R}_{+}\mapsto\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the index 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi,u$
\end_inset

 are concave, increasing and differentiable, this utility represents a convex
 preference relation and the set of subjective beliefs is a singleton consisting
 on a weighted mixture of all probabilities in the support of the measure
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (5)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\succeq$
\end_inset

 be a smooth model preference for which 
\begin_inset Formula $u$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 are concave, increasing and differentiable.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $\succeq$
\end_inset

 is a convex preference and 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\pi(f)=\frac{1}{||E_{\mu}[\phi'(E_{p}u(f)pDU(f)]||}E_{\mu}[\phi'(E_{p}u(f))pDU(f)].
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In particular, 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi(x)=\{E_{\mu}p\}$
\end_inset

 for all constant 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

