\[
B_{k}(p,w)=\left\{ c\in C_{k}:p\cdot c\leq w\right\} .
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Suppressing the endowment distribution: 
\begin_inset Formula $E=\{u,k,\pi,s\}$
\end_inset

 is the economy.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- Representative Economy, if every household is a representative household.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- For a representative household, we write 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{k}(p)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- For any set 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

, let 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta(X)$
\end_inset

 the set of simple probabilities.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu\in[0,1]^{X}$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $K(\mu)=\{x:\mu(x)>0\}$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum_{x\in X}\mu(x)=1$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(Y)=\sum_{x\in Y}\mu(x)$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $K(\mu)$
\end_inset

 is the support of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

.
 When 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is finite we identify 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta(X)$
\end_inset

 with the simplex.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- An allocation 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu\in\Delta(C)$
\end_inset

 is a probability on consumption plans.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
