\[
\sigma_{i}(\mu):=\sum_{c\in K(\mu)}c_{i}\cdot\mu(c)\leq s_{i}\quad\forall i\in N.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- For any 
\begin_inset Formula $C'\subset C$
\end_inset

, let 
\begin_inset Formula $M(C')$
\end_inset

 be the set of all feasible allocations that 
\begin_inset Formula $K(\mu)\subset C'.$
\end_inset

 Hence 
\begin_inset Formula $M(C_{k})$
\end_inset

 is the set of feasible allocation for the behavioral economy.
 Henceforth, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu\in M(C_{k})$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- The allocation 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is feasible in 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
