.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Conformable.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Two consumption plans 
\begin_inset Formula $c,c'$
\end_inset

 are conformable if 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{i}=c_{j}\iff c_{i}'=c_{j}'$
\end_inset

 they induce the same partition of 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $c\sim c'$
\end_inset

 are conformable.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(i) An allocation is simple if [
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(c)\cdot\mu(c')>0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $c\sim c'$
\end_inset

] implies 
\begin_inset Formula $c=c'$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(ii) An allocation is fair if 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(c)\cdot\mu(c')>0$
\end_inset

 implies 
\begin_inset Formula $U(c)=U(c')$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- A fair allocation yields the same utility to every household.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- A simple allocation, each partition of 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 has at most one consumption plan associated with it.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- If 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is simple the cardinality of 
\begin_inset Formula $K(\mu)$
\end_inset

 is at most equal to the number of partitions of 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 or fewer elements.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(iii) Monotonicity.
 Requires that consumption is weakly increasing in the aggregate endowment.
 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 is monotone if 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{i}\geq c_{j}$
\end_inset

 when 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{i}>s_{j}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(iv) Measurability.
 Means that the allocation remains feasible if states with identical endowments
 are combined into a single state.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{i}=c_{j}$
\end_inset

 when 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{i}=s_{j}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The allocation 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is monotone/measurable if 
\begin_inset Formula $\forall c\in K(\mu)$
\end_inset

 are monotone/measurable.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The mean utility 
\begin_inset Formula $W(\mu)$
\end_inset

 of allocation 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
W(\mu)=\sum_{c}U(c)\cdot\mu(c).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
The Planners Problem.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- We say that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu\in M(C_{k})$
\end_inset

 solves the planner's problem if 
\begin_inset Formula $W(\mu)\geq W(\mu')$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu'\in M(C_{k})$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
- The four properties hold when dealing with a strictly concave CRRA utility
 function.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{thm}
\end_layout

\end_inset

[Lemma.
 1] (i) There is a solution to the planner's problem.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(ii) Every solution to the planner's problem is simple, fair, monotone and
 measurable.
 
