\begin_layout Chapter
Final Paper
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Small pice, in the forma of a note or letter.
 The average lenght has to be 15pages including appendixes.
 Main body 10 pages.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
It has to establish a clear research question, a motivation, and literature
 review (this one short at most 1 page).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
It has to provide one answer that can (partially) respond to the research
 question.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
An empirical (revealed preference or similar) findings for or against some
 model.
 Classification, Identification.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Theoretical contributions.
 This can be a new model capturing a pheomenon that has not been explained
 (e.g., the choice overload).
 It can be an extension of a previous model.
 It can be a revealed preference characterization of a new model.
 It can be an application of a model (existing) to a market situation (e.g.,
 imperfect competition, portfolio allocation, general and partial equilibrium,
 BLP IO).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
A mix.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Experimental proposals, with some pilot.
 A pilot can be run using surveymonkey and similar tools.
 What matters here is that the design has to be new and interesting and
 it has to have a clear connection with the research question and what do
 we learn from this theoretically.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_body
